!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

traffic /ˈtræfɪk/

(trafficking,trafficked,traffics) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Traffic refers to all the vehicles that are moving along the roads in a particular area. 交通 [also 'the' N] 

例： There was heavy traffic on the roads. 路上的交通很拥挤。 

例： Traffic was unusually light for that time of day. 交通在白天的那个时段有些异常地顺畅。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Traffic refers to the movement of ships, trains, or aircraft between one place and another. Traffic also refers to the people and goods that are being transported. 运输; 人流; 货流 

例： Air traffic had returned to normal. 空中交通已恢复正常。 

3. N-UNCOUNT Traffic in something such as drugs or stolen goods is an illegal trade in them. (毒品或赃物等的) 非法买卖 

例： ...the widespread traffic in stolen cultural artefacts. …被盗文物非法买卖泛滥。 

4. V-I Someone who traffics in something such as drugs or stolen goods buys and sells them even though it is illegal to do so. 从事 (毒品或赃物等的) 非法买卖 

例： The president said illegal drugs are hurting the entire world and anyone who traffics in them should be brought to justice. 总统说毒品正在危害全世界，毒品非法交易者都应该绳之以法。 

5. trafficking N-UNCOUNT 非法买卖 

例： He was sentenced to ten years in prison on charges of drug trafficking. 他被指控贩毒，被判10年徒刑。

